## TypeScript Standards

- 🔴 **Use strict typing** for all variables, parameters, and return types
- 🔴 **Avoid `any` type** - Use `unknown` or specific types instead
- 🟠 **Use interfaces** over type aliases for object definitions
- 🟡 **Implement proper generics** for reusable code
- 🔴 **Properly type event emitters and observables**
- 🟠 **Use readonly properties** for immutable data
- 🟡 **Use union types** instead of boolean parameters

---

## Database & ORM Best Practices

- 🔴 **Use proper TypeScript models** with the ORM (TypeORM, Prisma, etc.)
- 🟠 **Implement database migrations** for schema changes
- 🟡 **Use transactions** for multi-step operations
- 🟠 **Implement proper indexing** for performance
- 🟡 **Use soft deletes** where appropriate for data retention
- 🟠 **Avoid N+1 queries** - Use eager loading when needed
- 🔴 **Never skip validation** at the database level

---

## API Documentation

- 🟠 **Use Swagger/OpenAPI** decorators for all endpoints
- 🟡 **Document all parameters and responses**
- 🟡 **Provide meaningful descriptions** for operations
- 🟠 **Include example requests and responses**
- 🟡 **Document error responses** with proper HTTP status codes

---

## Dependency Injection & Configuration

- 🔴 **Use NestJS dependency injection** for all dependencies
- 🟠 **Configure environment variables** properly with validation
- 🟡 **Use @Inject() for optional dependencies** or non-class providers
- 🔴 **Avoid circular dependencies** - Refactor if detected
- 🟠 **Use lazy initialization** for expensive resources
- 🟡 **Implement proper lifecycle hooks** (onModuleInit, onModuleDestroy, etc.)

---

## Security Best Practices

- 🔴 **Validate all inputs** using DTOs and class-validator
- 🔴 **Sanitize inputs** to prevent injection attacks
- 🟠 **Implement proper authentication** and authorization
- 🟠 **Use HTTPS** in production
- 🟡 **Implement rate limiting** for sensitive endpoints
- 🟠 **Hash passwords** with proper algorithms
- 🔴 **Never log sensitive data** (passwords, tokens, etc.)
- 🟡 **Implement CORS** properly with whitelist

---

## Logging & Monitoring

- 🟠 **Use NestJS Logger** for consistent logging
- 🟠 **Log at appropriate levels** (debug, log, warn, error)
- 🟡 **Include context** in log messages for debugging
- 🟡 **Avoid logging sensitive information**
- 🟠 **Monitor performance** of critical operations
- 🟡 **Implement health checks** for dependencies

---

## Performance Optimization

- 🟡 **Use pagination** for large datasets
- 🟠 **Implement proper indexing** in databases
- 🟡 **Use caching** appropriately (Redis, in-memory)
- 🟠 **Batch operations** when possible
- 🟡 **Implement query optimization** and monitoring
- 🟠 **Avoid unnecessary operations** in loops

---

## Code Organization & Naming

- 🔴 **Use PascalCase** for class names
- 🔴 **Use camelCase** for variables and methods
- 🟠 **Use UPPER_CASE** for constants
- 🟡 **Use descriptive names** that reveal intent
- 🟠 **Group related code** together logically
- 🟡 **Keep file size reasonable** - Split large files
- 🟡 **Use consistent file naming** conventions

